	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is actually a great spell, AE groups rock!<BR>
<BR>
Ingredients:<BR>
1x good chanter<BR>
1x good cleric<BR>
1x puller (any tank/quasi-tank will do)<BR>
3x AE nukers - wizzies are best, but it is good to have a mage in there and druids OK too.<BR>
<BR>
Method:<BR>
Puller agro's 6-10 mobs bringing them all back to the group.  Chanter chains AE stuns while everyone else (even the cleric*) opens up with their AE spells.<BR>
<BR>
Result:<BR>
6-10 mobs dead in ~30 seconds = insane XP.<BR>
<BR>
For even better results have 2 groups so that second chanter can AE Tash once, and maybe have a Shaman AE slow.  Pity there is no AE Malise.<BR>
<BR>
At level 55 I get over a blue an hour using this method in KC doing hands/wl/basement/DC/anything else stupid enough to get in the road.<BR>
<BR>
* Cleric AE has long recast delay, so they get to cast once then go back to healing (MUST keep the chanter alive at all costs)....but at least they get to do some damage for once.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
